Cryptography is a part of computer science and mathematics that focuses on
protecting contents of transmitted data through insecure channels like internet,
from unauthorized parties. It's name is derived from the greek word "kryptos"
which means hidden and "graphein" meaning writing so we could literally
translate it as hidden writing. In today's world it is possible to hide any
type of digital communication. To achieve this it relies on hard mathematical
problems which are almost impossible to solve without knowing .
